    "body" : "<pre><code>if(resultSet.first) {\n\n} else { \n    system.out.println(\"No raw or resultSet is empty\");\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Because if ResultSet has no raw then <code>resultSet.first</code> returns false.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1977520,
      "reputation" : 500,
      "user_id" : 1774981,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/aaff472013796de603ea366bdd189fd9?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Dermot Doherty",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1774981/dermot-doherty"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 15,
    "last_activity_date" : 1355334993,
    "creation_date" : 1355334993,
    "answer_id" : 13845772,
    "question_id" : 867194,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Best to use ResultSet.next() along with the do {...} while() syntax for this.</p>\n\n<p>The \"check for any results\" call ResultSet.next() moves the cursor to the first row, so use the do {...} while() syntax to process that row while continuing to process remaining rows returned by the loop.</p>\n\n<p>This way you get to check for any results, while at the same time also processing any results returned.</p>\n\n<pre><code>if(resultSet.next()) { // Checks for any results and moves cursor to first row,\n    do { // Use 'do...while' to process the first row, while continuing to process remaining rows\n\n    } while (resultSet.next());\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1511192,
      "reputation" : 217,
      "user_id" : 1413278,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/742c01334bccee42b4a765b54c68a144?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Deepu Surendran",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1413278/deepu-surendran"
    },
