    "creation_date" : 1400604101,
    "answer_id" : 23765510,
    "question_id" : 867194,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Initially, the result set object (rs) points to the BFR (before first record). Once we use rs.next(), the cursor points to the first record and the rs holds \"true\". Using the while loop you can print all the records of the table. After all the records are retrieved, the cursor moves to ALR (After last record) and it will be set to null. Let us consider that there are 2 records in the table.</p>\n\n<pre><code>if(rs.next()==false){\n    // there are no records found\n    }    \n\nwhile (rs.next()==true){\n    // print all the records of the table\n    }\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>In short hand, we can also write the condition as while (rs.next()).    </p>\n"
  }, {
