    "answer_id" : 42779813,
    "question_id" : 867194,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I think the easiest way for checking result set is via <strong>CollectionUtils</strong> under package <strong>org.apache.commons.collections.CollectionUtils</strong></p>\n\n<pre><code>if(CollectionUtils.isNotEmpty(resultList)){\n  /**\n  * do some stuff\n  */\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This will check for null as well as empty result set condition. </p>\n\n<p>For more detail information you can refer to the following doc. \n<a href=\"https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-collections/javadocs/api-release/org/apache/commons/collections4/CollectionUtils.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">CollectionUtils</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2385716,
      "reputation" : 399,
      "user_id" : 3586682,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/16399baf044666843ecdf120dd4089b6?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "stiebrs",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3586682/stiebrs"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1507713083,
    "creation_date" : 1507713083,
    "answer_id" : 46684273,
    "question_id" : 867194,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Why not use rs.getRow()?</p>\n\n<pre><code>int getRow()\n           throws SQLException\nRetrieves the current row number. The first row is number 1, the second number 2, and so on.\nNote:Support for the getRow method is optional for ResultSets with a result set type of TYPE_FORWARD_ONLY\n\nReturns:\nthe current row number; 0 if there is no current row\nThrows:\nSQLException - if a database access error occurs or this method is called on a closed result set\nSQLFeatureNotSupportedException - if the JDBC driver does not support this method\nSince:\n1.2\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>For me check \"if (rs.getRow() != 0)\" seems to work just fine.</p>\n"
  }, {
